Wash and dry produce. Drain and rinse @chickpeas{1%400g can}; pat dry with #paper towels{}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced) greens (save whites for another use). Trim root end from @baby lettuce{1}(root end trimmed); roughly chop. Toast @sourdough bread{4%slices} in a #toaster{} until golden.

Place chickpeas in a #medium bowl{}; mash with the back of a #fork{} until about half the chickpeas are smooth (leave some larger chickpea pieces for texture-packed bites!). Stir in scallion greens, @vegan mayo{6%tablespoons}, @Frank's Seasoning Blend{1/4%ounce}, and @Frank's Hot Sauce{1} until combined.

> Use less Frank's Seasoning Blend and hot sauce if you prefer less heat!

== Green Salad ==

In a #large bowl{}, combine half the @white wine vinegar{2%teaspoons}, a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoons}, and a big pinch of @sugar{1/2%teaspoon} (we used ½ tsp).

> Use 4 teaspoons white wine vinegar and 1 tsp sugar for 4 servings.

Add lettuce and toss to coat; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Assembly ==

Divide chickpea filling between half the toasted bread slices; top each with a handful of green salad. Close sandwiches; halve crosswise.

Divide sandwiches between plates. Serve with @blue corn tortilla chips{1.5%ounces} and remaining green salad on the side.